From: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
Subject: kABI workaround for struct uart_8250_port changes
Patch-mainline: Never, kABI workaround
References: bsc#1262480

The patch
  patches.suse/Revert-serial-8250-Switch-to-nbcon-console.patch
removed a couple of fields from struct uart_8250_port as they are no
longer used, which broke kABI, unfortunately.

Revive them just as placeholders for keeping kABI compatibility.

Reviewed-by: Jan Kara <jack@suse.cz>
Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 include/linux/serial_8250.h |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/include/linux/serial_8250.h
+++ b/include/linux/serial_8250.h
@@ -151,7 +151,9 @@ struct uart_8250_port {
 	u16			lsr_saved_flags;
 	u16			lsr_save_mask;
 #define MSR_SAVE_FLAGS UART_MSR_ANY_DELTA
+	bool			console_line_ended; /* FIXME: kABI placeholder*/
 	unsigned char		msr_saved_flags;
+	struct irq_work		modem_status_work; /* FIXME: kABI placeholder*/
 
 	struct uart_8250_dma	*dma;
 	const struct uart_8250_ops *ops;
